##################----INSTALL TOMCAT----##################
Set up server- Tomcat can run on T2 medium
Update server 
    $sudo apt update
Install latest version of java
sudo apt install default-jdk
Create user or continue as Ubuntu user
    $useradd -s /bin/bash -d /home/mytomcatuser -m -G sudo mytomcatuser
create password
     $passwd mytomcatuser
Enter password
Switch to Tomcat user
    $su - mytomcatuser
Download latest version of Tomcat
    $sudo wget https://archive.apache.org/dist/tomcat/tomcat-9/v9.0.65/bin/apache-tomcat-9.0.65.tar.gz   OR
    $sudo wget https://dlcdn.apache.org/tomcat/tomcat-9/v9.0.80/bin/apache-tomcat-9.0.80.tar.gz (Another link )

Unzip tar file
     $sudo tar -xvf apache-tomcat-9.0.65.tar.gz
Optional- rename apache-tomcat-9.0.65. to Tomcat

--> Change directory to Tomcat and  move to conf directory and change port in tomcat server to another port from default port 
(default port for Tomcat is 8080. This is also port for Jenkins. To run an effective pipeline, Update Tomcat default port to something else. In this case 8090)
     $vi server.xml
scroll down to connector port and change port address: change from 8080 to 8090
input public IP of your instance plus port no on the web. This should display Tomcat web browser

Update tomcat users xml file for manager app login.
     $vi tomcat-users.xml
Update roles
 <role rolename="manager-gui"/>
  <role rolename="manager-script"/>
  <role rolename="admin-gui"/>
  <role rolename="admin-script"/>
 <role rolename="admin-manager"/>
  <user username="yourtomcatuser" password="your password" roles="manager-gui,manager-script,admin-gui,admin-script,admin-manager"/>
save
:wq!
cd to webapps and update hostmanager and manager files
vi host-manager/META-INF/context.xml
scroll to  allow="127\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+|::1|0:0:0:0:0:0:0:1|.*" />   only add |,*
   $ vi manager/META-INF/context.xml
do same as above and save
change directory back to Tomcat
   $cd ..
create a symbolic links for direct start and stop of tomcat
   $ sudo ln -s /home/yourtomcatuser/Tomcat/bin/shutdown.sh/usr/local/bin/stopTomcat
   $sudo ln -s /home/yourtomcatuser/Tomcat/bin/startup.sh/usr/local/bin/startTomcat
   $startTomcat
   $stopTomcat

